Sentencas: For metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells, gadolinium-doped cerium ceria (GDC) is one of the most promising electrolyte materials due to its high ionic conductivity at medium and low temperatures.
Titulo: Preparation of Plasma Sprayed GDC Electrolytes for Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, using traditional sintering method to prepare GDC electrolytes at high temperature can lead to interdiffusion between the metal supports, electrolytes, and electrodes, which can seriously impact cell performance.
Titulo: Preparation of Plasma Sprayed GDC Electrolytes for Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this paper, the GDC electrolytes were prepared using atmospheric plasma spraying technology, which could avoid the issue of high-temperature sintering.
Titulo: Preparation of Plasma Sprayed GDC Electrolytes for Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The effects of different spraying distances on the microstructure, interface, and cell performance were studied.
Titulo: Preparation of Plasma Sprayed GDC Electrolytes for Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results show that the cell performance is optimal when the spraying distance is 80 mm.
Titulo: Preparation of Plasma Sprayed GDC Electrolytes for Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The open-circuit voltages of the single cell at 500, 600, and 700 degrees C are 0.866 V, 0.82 V, and 0.75 V, respectively.
Titulo: Preparation of Plasma Sprayed GDC Electrolytes for Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The peak power densities at these temperatures are 66.2, 182.8, and 386 mW/cm2, respectively.
Titulo: Preparation of Plasma Sprayed GDC Electrolytes for Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It provides a reference value for the commercialization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells prepared by plasma spraying.
Titulo: Preparation of Plasma Sprayed GDC Electrolytes for Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
